The pistol that Harrison Ford's character Han Solo used in Star Wars: The Empire Strikes Back and The Return of the Jedi is being sold.

The so-called DL-44 Blaster - which Ford used in the two 1980s blockbuster movies - is estimated to be sold for between $200,000 to $300,000 when it goes up for auction.

It is being sold by a memorabilia collector, and is still in its original condition, only showing signs of wear from its use.

