It's the same prop Darth Vader lassoed 
out of Solo's hand and the one which Ford wrestled back from a 
Stormtrooper, said online auctioneeers Invaluable on their website.

They said: 'The blaster is exactly in its original filming condition and therefore exhibits wear from use, but retains all of the original details, including the flash suppressor and scope.'

Its vintage boxy design was inspired by the Mauser C96, a German pistol made in large numbers from 1896 to 1937.

The item is open for bidding alongside other pistols and guns used by Ford in Blade Runner and Indiana Jones and the Kingdom of the Crystal Skull.

